<body>
	<div class="preorder">
  		<!-- <a class="btn" href="/docs/blog">Blog</a> -->
  		<button data-celery="genius" class="btn btn-primary"><%= Settings.call_to_action %></button>
  	</div>

	<style>
		.play-button {
			margin-top: 100px;
			display: block;
			margin-left: auto;
			margin-right: auto;
		}
		.play-button:hover {
			cursor: pointer;
		}
		#video {
			width: 580px;
			height: 500px;
		}
		.video {
			background: url("assets/background/background-home3.png") no-repeat center center fixed;
			background-size: cover;
			-webkit-background-size: cover;
			-o-background-size: cover;
			-moz-background-size: cover;
			height: 700px;
		}
		.monitor-banner {
			background: url("assets/background/NotificationInEmergency_Background.png") no-repeat center center fixed;
			background-size: cover;
			-webkit-background-size: cover;
			-o-background-size: cover;
			-moz-background-size: cover;
			height: 900px;
		}
		.h-desc {
			text-align: center;
		}
		h1.tlt {
			font-size: 85px;
			color: #6b6b6b;
		}
	</style>

	<script>
		$(function() {

			$('.tlt').textillate({
				in: {
					effect: 'fadeInLeftBig',
					sync: true,
					shuffle: false
				},
				out: {
					effect: 'fadeOutRightBig',
					sync: true,
					shuffle: false
				}
			});

			var playBtn = $('#play-button');
			var videoModal = $('#video-modal');
			var iframe = document.getElementById('video');
			var player = $f(iframe);
			var play = $(iframe);

			playBtn.hover(function() {
				var img = this;
				img.src = '/assets/icons/play-button2-light.png';
			}, function() {
				var img = this;
				img.src = '/assets/icons/play-button2.png';
			});

			playBtn.click(function() {
				videoModal.modal();
				player.api('play');
			});

			videoModal.on('hide.bs.modal', function(e) {
				player.api('pause');
			});
		});
	</script>

	<div class="video">
		<div class="container">
			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-md-12">
					<div class="logo">
						<a href="/"><img src="/assets/logo.png" /></a>
					</div>
					<div class="h-desc">
						<h1 class="tlt">
							<ul class="texts">
								<li data-in-effect="fadeIn">Redefine Security</li>
								<li data-in-effect="fadeIn">No Contract</li>
								<li data-in-effect="fadeIn">Picture Notification</li>
							</ul>
						</h1>
					</div>
					<img id="play-button" class="play-button" src="/assets/icons/play-button2.png" />
				</div>
				<div id="video-modal" class="modal fade">
				  <div class="modal-dialog">
				    <div class="modal-content">
				        <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-hidden="true">&times;</button>
				        <iframe src="//player.vimeo.com/video/80312270?api=1" frameborder="0" webkitallowfullscreen mozallowfullscreen allowfullscreen id="video"></iframe>
				      </div>
				    </div><!-- /.modal-content -->
				  </div><!-- /.modal-dialog -->
				</div><!-- /.modal -->
			</div>
		</div>	
	</div>

	<div class="big_wrapper">
	  <div class="wrapper" id="one">
	    <div class="point_copy">
	      <h2>
	        Security without a contract
	      </h2>
	      <p>
	       No binding contracts! Genius will provide your home with discrete security in the palm of your hand. 
	      <p>
	    </div>
	  </div>
	</div>

	<div class="big_wrapper">
	  <div class="wrapper" id="two">
	    <div class="point_copy right">
	      <h2 style="text-align: center;">
	        Genius will bring you peace of mind
	      </h2>
	      <p>
	        Know that you will be notified of an intrusion or an emergency immediately when it happens. 
	      <p>
	    </div>
	  </div>
	</div>

	<div class="big_wrapper">
	  <div class="wrapper" id="three">
	    <div class="point_copy">
	      <h2>
	        Your system, you control it.
	      </h2>
	      <p>
	        Place the sensor anywhere on your selling and when the alarm trips a picture is sent to your phone. The power is in your hand to decide what to do next.
	      <p>
	    </div>
	  </div>
	  <div class="wrapper">
	    <p class="seemore-who"><a href="/docs/who">See more on if Genius is for you ... </a></p>
	  </div>
	</div>

	<div class="gray_background">
	  <ul class="wrapper clearfix" id="other_points">
	    <li id="section-1">
	      <h3>Secures Any Home</h3>
	      <p>Place Genius comfortably in any home. If you move, easily take the device with you.</p>
	    </li>
	    <li id="section-2">
	      <h3>Easy Install</h3>
	      <p>With no professional installation required, you can install your Genius device using mounting tape in minutes.</p>
	    </li>
	    <li id="section-3">
	      <h3>Advanced Motion Detection</h3>
	      <p>Utilizing the best technology available, Genius is smart enough to know if your house cat is causing a stir versus a legitimate intrusion.</p>
	    </li>
	    <li id="section-4">
	      <h3>Cordless and Discrete</h3>
	      <p>Battery powered sensor devices do not need a cord, allowing you to put Genius wherever you need it.</p>
	    </li>
	    <p id="section-7"><a href="/docs/product">See more on how Genius works ...</a></p>
	  </ul>
	</div>

	<div class="big_wrapper">
	  <div class="wrapper center" id="middle_reserve">
	    <h2><%= Settings.ships %></h2>
	    <a href="/preorder/checkout" class="btn btn-primary reserve"><%= Settings.middle_reserve_text %></a>
	  </div>
	</div> 

	<div class="gray_background" id="faqs">
	  <div class="wrapper clearfix">
	    <h4>Frequently Asked Questions</h4>
	    <ul>
	      <li class=''>
	        <details class=''>
	          <summary class=''>How do I setup Amazon Payments?</summary>
	          <p>You'll need to <a href="https://payments.amazon.com/sdui/sdui/accountstatus">create an Amazon Seller Central account</a>. Afterwards, get your access key and secret key from the "Integration" tab on your AWS account. <a href="https://payments.amazon.com/sdui/sdui/helpTab/Checkout-by-Amazon/Advanced-Integration-Help/Using-Your-Access-Key">Click here for more info</a>.
	          <br />
	          <br />
	          Once you have your access key and secret key, head over to <code>config/settings.yml</code>. Change <code>amazon_access_key</code> and <code>amazon_secret_key</code> appropriately.</p>
	        </details>
	      </li>
	      <li>
	        <details class=''>
	          <summary>Can I use another payments provider?</summary>
	          <p>Of course. We haven't built in support for other providers, but we recommend that you take a look at <a href="https://stripe.com">Stripe</a> or <a href="https://wepay.com">WePay</a>.</p>
	        </details>
	      </li>
	      <li>
	        <details class=''>
	          <summary>How do I edit the FAQ?</summary>
	          <p>The faq is a partial located in <code>app/views/preorder/homepage/_faq.html.erb</code> The <code>summary</code> tag is the title, the <code>p</code> is the body. Make sure to add an <code>li</code> tag for each FAQ entry.</p>
	        </details>
	      </li>
	      <li>
	        <details class=''>
	          <summary>How do I change around the images, product name, etc?</summary>
	          <p>The best way is in <code>config/settings.yml</code>. It has variables for several different parts, the video, the product name, the call to action button ("Fork Now"), and several more.
	          </p>
	        </details>
	      </li>
	    </ul>
	    <ul class='col2'>
	      <li>
	        <details class=''>
	          <summary>How do I change the CSS?</summary>
	          <p>Head over to <code>app/assets/stylesheets/variables.css.scss</code>. It makes it easy to change around the elements used throughout the HTML.
	          <br />
	          <br />
	          Alternatively, you can dive right into the CSS, have a look at <code>app/assets/stylesheets/main.css.scss</code>.</p>
	        </details>
	      </li>
	      <li class=''>
	        <details class=''>
	          <summary>Why did you release this?</summary>
	          <p>Hardware startups are less welcome on Kickstarter than they were 6 months ago. We needed to roll our own kickstarter, so we did. Other hardware startups probably will too, so we made it easier for them by open sourcing our way of doing it.</p>
	        </details>
	      </li>
	      <li class=''>
	        <details class=''>
	          <summary class=''>What software stack does this use?</summary>
	          <p>It's a Ruby on Rails app that makes heavy use of SCSS, Kickstarter's wonderful <code>amazon_flex_pay</code> gem, and a hint of CoffeeScript.</p>
	        </details>
	      </li>
	      <li class=''>
	        <details class=''>
	          <summary class=''>How do I deploy it?</summary>
	          <p>We recommend using Heroku. We include a Procfile for you, so all you need to do is:
	          <p>
	            <p>Install the <a href="https://toolbelt.heroku.com/">Heroku Toolbelt</a></p>
	            <p>Run <code>heroku create</code> in Selfstarter's folder</code></p>
	            <p>Run <code>git push heroku master</code> in Selfstarter's folder</p>
	          </p>
	        </details>
	      </li>
	    </ul>
	  </div>
	</div>
	<div id='logos'>
	  <ul class="wrapper clearfix">
	    <li id="awesomeblog"><a href=""></a></li>
	    <li id="coolpaper"><a href=""></a></li>
	    <li id="nicemag"><a href=""></a></li>
	    <li id="readcrunch"><a href=""></a></li>
	  </ul>
	</div>
	<%= render 'layouts/footer' %>
</body>


